[Total Exposure Control] Removed the automatic brand-based filtering logic. Now, all shooting sequences are exposed at the top of the code as native Python lists for maximum editing freedom.

[Separation of Astronomical Targets] Clearly split shutter speeds into two independent pools: SHUTTER_SPEEDS_PROMINENCES (ultra-fast speeds to preserve plasma details and avoid red channel saturation) and SHUTTER_SPEEDS_CORONA (a dynamic exposure ramp for the outer filaments).

[File Renaming Removal (Zero Overhead)] Eliminated software-side file renaming and live cable transfers during the core loop. The script now sends a pure capture command: the camera saves natively to the internal SD card (e.g., IMG_XXXX.CR3), leveraging the camera's hardware buffer without USB bottlenecks.

[3-Shot Safety Burst] Implemented a triple consecutive burst for every single stop of the HDR ladder. This ensures high statistical redundancy against micro-blur/vibrations and provides more clean frames for post-production stacking.